  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 4.64,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. A LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 5.58,
      "end": 9.76,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 11.06,
      "end": 14.22,
      "text": "It stops Fables, the Ox and the Frog.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 15.76,
      "end": 21.14,
      "text": "Two little frogs were playing about at the edge of a pool when an ox came down to the water to drink,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 21.82,
      "end": 24.86,
      "text": "and by accident trod on one of them and crushed the life out of him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 25.9,
      "end": 28.88,
      "text": "When the old frog missed him, she asked his brother where he was.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 29.36,
      "end": 31.8,
      "text": "He is dead mother, said the little frog.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 32.34,
      "end": 37.24,
      "text": "An enormous big creature with four legs came to our pool this morning and trampled him down in the mud.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 38.46,
      "end": 40.56,
      "text": "Enormous, was he? Was he as big as this?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 41.0,
      "end": 44.12,
      "text": "Said the frog, puffing herself out to look as big as possible.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 44.7,
      "end": 47.62,
      "text": "Oh yes, much bigger was the answer.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 48.46,
      "end": 50.76,
      "text": "The frog puffed herself out still more.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 51.66,
      "end": 53.14,
      "text": "Was he as big as this?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 53.52,
      "end": 54.06,
      "text": "Said she.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 54.06,
      "end": 57.32,
      "text": "Oh yes, yes mother, much bigger.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 57.8,
      "end": 58.54,
      "text": "Said the little frog.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 59.46,
      "end": 64.14,
      "text": "And yet again, she puffed and puffed herself out until she was almost as round as a ball.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 64.64,
      "end": 67.8,
      "text": "As big as she began, but then she burst.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 69.18,
      "end": 71.32,
      "text": "End of the Ox and the Frog.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
